oai_dc:dc.dc:title: For Whom Will You Be Working in the Year 2000
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Siebert, John
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Our first speaker today is Dr. John Siebert. John is a Petaluma, California boy who got his Masters and Ph.D. at the University of California, Berkley. He was an extension economist at Purdue University from 1978 to 1981. He became the extension economist at U .C. Davis from 1981 to 1985, and presently is the economist with the California Cooperative Creamery in Petaluma. His special recognition according to John is that he has put his foot in his mouth in almost every county in Indiana and California and so now he wants to spread it to Arizona.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1987; 77-82
